			<postalcode><![CDATA[94401]]></postalcode>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The Logistics Coordinator is a key member of the operations team with responsibility over our warehouse activities, logistics and purchases. This is a hands on role suited for someone with experience in logistics / operations, the ability to involve and align multiple stakeholders and to grow professionally in a fast paced environment.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Key responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage operations at our warehouse facility:
<ul>
<li>
Coordinate monthly activities with our fulfillment partners: monthly kitting and shipping.</li>
<li>
Oversee quality control program.</li>
<li>
Monitor warehouse&rsquo;s performance and ensure service level&rsquo;s consistency.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
Manage and execute international and domestic logistics:
<ul>
<li>
Coordinate domestic logistics with brand partners.</li>
<li>
Transport and import products from international sources (mainly China).</li>
<li>
Manage shipping program to end customers by working closely with fulfillment partners and carriers.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
Manage purchases:
<ul>
<li>
Track inventory of supplies for production activities, follow purchase cycle, negotiate price and volume schedule with vendors.</li>
<li>
Source and select local and international suppliers.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
Drive for operational excellence:
<ul>
<li>
Design processes to improve customers&rsquo; experience.</li>
<li>
Maintain KPI programs and actively create actions plans based on observed results.</li>
<li>
Design and implement strategies to improve the quality of all warehouse activities.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Must-Have Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor degree, preferably in a related field.</li>
<li>
4 to 7 years of experience managing logistics preferably in direct to consumer e-commerce company.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Extremely organized, detailed oriented and able to communicate effectively with partners, suppliers and other ispy management.</li>
<li>
Experience in international logistics; knowledge of main players, imports and customs processes.</li>
<li>
First hand contact with major national carriers and importers, including trucking companies.</li>
<li>
Experience managing 3PLs, enforcing contracts and service levels.</li>
<li>
Ability to manage time effectively, set priorities and work in a team environment.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>About ipsy:</strong><br />
ipsy is an online community that inspires women around the world to express their unique beauty.&nbsp; With videos from our well-loved YouTube stylists, including co-founder Michelle Phan, as well as from our devoted and engaged user community, we are changing the way women learn about and experience beauty looks. We are looking for passionate and creative people to join our team. Our Glam Bag program delivers make up products to over 150,000 subscribers each month.</p>
<p>
Based at our beautiful new HQ in San Mateo, ipsy is funded by top-tier VCs and angel investors. Watch a video about working at ipsy.</p>
<p>
Please check us out at ipsy.com and on Facebook!</p>
]]></description>
