			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The Customer Service Manager will be responsible for providing a consistent and delightful experience to ipsy members. Her or his voice will represent ipsy across different channels. We are looking for someone with several years managing and developing customer service programs and deep understanding of customer communications including social media. The Customer Service Manager is passionate about beauty, understands our customers&rsquo; concerns and relentlessly works to improve their experience.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
Further develop ipsy&rsquo;s customer experience:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Understand customer touch points and develop strategies to care for and delight customers at every opportunity.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Work closely with marketing team to develop communication tools and messages.</li>
<li>
Develop policies to address current and new customer care scenarios with creative and brand-appropriate solutions.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Manage customer care team:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Lead and motivate ipsyCare team.&nbsp; Provide feedback and development opportunities for team members.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Monitor the performance of each member and provide coaching opportunities as necessary.</li>
<li>
Drive staffing plan by hiring, training and retaining ipsyCare staff.</li>
<li>
Personally resolve escalated cases.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Manage customer care communications:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Actively monitor all communication channels including Facebook and other social media platforms.&nbsp; Identify customer issues or concerns and work with team to address.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Develop and write all communication messages for customer-facing events (shipping, billing, quality issues, etc.) to be used across all platforms.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Drive improvement plan:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop and keep track of key performance indicators.</li>
<li>
Strategically leverage customer feedback to drive continuous improvement in a quantifiable manner.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent.</li>
<li>
3+ years of customer service management experience, in a customer facing e-commerce company.</li>
<li>
Outstanding leadership and management skills with proven ability to build and develop a customer service team.</li>
<li>
Excellent writing skills</li>
<li>
Knowledge of customer&rsquo;s service systems, infrastructure, reporting and metrics. Social media understanding is preferred.</li>
<li>
Ability to gather, synthesize and analyze information from discrete sources.</li>
<li>
Excellent presentation and verbal communication skills.</li>
<li>
Flexible work schedules (weekends and/or evenings).</li>
<li>
Passionate about the customer experience.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
About ipsy:<br />
ipsy is an online community that inspires women around the world to express their unique beauty.&nbsp; With videos from our well-loved YouTube stylists, including co-founder Michelle Phan, as well as from our devoted and engaged user community, we are changing the way women learn about and experience beauty looks. We are looking for passionate and creative people to join our team. Our Glam Bag program delivers make up products to over 150,000 subscribers each month.</p>
<p>
Based at our beautiful new HQ in San Mateo, ipsy is funded by top-tier VCs and angel investors. Watch a video about working at ipsy.</p>
